got that from you.

18:06.786 --> 18:08.777
We've been friends
for a long time now.

18:08.921 --> 18:10.719
JOANIE:
You go first, Fonz.

18:14.060 --> 18:16.427
I wonder who it's from, Fonzie.

18:17.463 --> 18:19.397
It's from my old man.

18:19.532 --> 18:21.057
Oh!

18:21.200 --> 18:22.929
(whispers):
Mom...

18:33.746 --> 18:36.909
"Son...

18:37.049 --> 18:40.417
"I'm writing this letter
in case I don't have the guts

18:40.553 --> 18:43.682
"to tell you it was me
that delivered the letter.

18:49.061 --> 18:52.395
I'm not sure how
you're gonna take this..."

18:53.766 --> 18:56.133
Oh, Arthur, are you all right?

18:56.268 --> 18:58.327
He's not sure how
I'm gonna take this.

18:58.471 --> 19:00.496
I haven't seen him
since I was three years old!

19:00.640 --> 19:02.267
How does he think
I'm gonna take this?!

19:02.408 --> 19:05.139
Probably just the way you are.

19:05.277 --> 19:08.110
- Look, what's going on here?
- FONZIE: Nothing.

19:08.247 --> 19:09.408
I-It's nothing.
Don't worry about it.

19:09.548 --> 19:10.982
RICHIE:
It is, too, something, Fonz.

19:11.117 --> 19:13.381
And you can't keep ignoring it.
This is your father!

19:13.519 --> 19:14.884
He's my father.
Then why didn't he stay?

19:15.021 --> 19:16.750
Why didn't he talk to me?
Why'd he walk out

19:16.889 --> 19:19.017
when I was three years old?
I didn't even get a chance

19:19.158 --> 19:20.887
to see his face real good.

19:21.027 --> 19:22.290
He hates me. That's it.

19:22.428 --> 19:23.520
Oh, Arthur!

19:23.663 --> 19:25.825
No, no, no, don't worry
about it. I accept it.

19:25.965 --> 19:28.525
Walked out on me 'cause he hates
my guts. It's all right.

19:28.668 --> 19:32.866
I didn't even get a chance
to see his face real good.

19:33.005 --> 19:34.996
<i>II</i>

19:39.478 --> 19:40.707
Now, wait a minute, Richard.

19:40.846 --> 19:42.280
- That's Fonz...
- Dad, I've been hearing

19:42.415 --> 19:45.407
about Fonzie's father
ever since I met him.

19:47.086 --> 19:49.521
Fonzie, I want to know
what you're afraid of.

19:49.655 --> 19:51.521
I'm not afraid of anything.

19:51.657 --> 19:54.490
You want to read it, read it.

19:54.627 --> 19:56.288
All right.

20:00.633 --> 20:03.830
"I was a merchant seaman
when I met your ma."

20:04.870 --> 20:06.861
My ma.

20:08.708 --> 20:12.941
"I thought I could settle down
like everybody else.

20:13.079 --> 20:14.911
"Maybe it was my fault.

20:15.047 --> 20:16.742
"I don't know.

20:16.882 --> 20:19.044
"It just didn't work out.

20:20.720 --> 20:24.020
"I can't stay
in one place too long.

20:24.156 --> 20:27.148
"I know it's not much
of an explanation, but...

20:27.293 --> 20:31.025
that's the way it was."

20:31.163 --> 20:33.723
And signed:
"Your father...

20:33.866 --> 20:35.994
Vito Fonzarelli."

20:40.239 --> 20:42.708
Oh, Arthur, your father...

20:42.842 --> 20:44.776
Father? You call that a father?

20:44.910 --> 20:47.072
Oh, Howard, now,
don't be too hard on him.

20:47.213 --> 20:49.773
- He explained... -He didn't
explain anything, Marion.

20:49.915 --> 20:51.815
- Dad...
- Look, Richard,

20:51.951 --> 20:55.080
every man comes to that moment
when he wants to run away

20:55.221 --> 20:56.746
from everything he's got

20:56.889 --> 20:59.415
and go bum around
through the Seven Seas.

20:59.558 --> 21:01.083
But most of them don't.

21:01.227 --> 21:03.161
Howard, will you
just try to understand?

21:03.295 --> 21:04.660
I do understand, Marion.

21:04.797 --> 21:06.993
I understand that there's
something called responsibility,

21:07.133 --> 21:09.693
and this man
just couldn't face up to his.

21:10.736 --> 21:12.329
I'm sorry, Fonzie,

21:12.471 --> 21:16.567
I know it's none of my business,
but that's the way I feel.

21:17.743 --> 21:19.233
Whoa!

21:23.315 --> 21:25.784
- I feel great.
- You what?

21:25.918 --> 21:28.114
- Feel great?
- I feel great.

21:28.254 --> 21:29.847
See, I understand now.

21:29.989 --> 21:32.856
Uh, what you're talking here.
It's not my fault.

21:32.992 --> 21:34.721
You see, I thought
it was my fault.

21:34.860 --> 21:37.295
I thought I did something wrong
that made him leave, you know?

21:37.429 --> 21:39.693
But, Fonzie,
you were just a kid!

21:39.832 --> 21:41.493
Yeah, I know.
I thought I did something wrong,

21:41.634 --> 21:43.227
you know, like getting born.

21:44.336 --> 21:46.361
But I don't feel
so much hate anymore.

21:46.505 --> 21:47.631
You know what I mean?

21:47.773 --> 21:50.333
I understand what
you were talking about.

21:50.476 --> 21:52.342
Couldn't help himself.

21:52.478 --> 21:54.537
It's all right.
Some people are like that.

21:54.680 --> 21:58.446
You know how good it feels
not to hate anymore?

21:58.584 --> 22:00.575
It feels good.

